  "title": "CLASS 4 DRIVER",
  "description": "<h3><u><strong>Job Description:</strong></u></h3><p>We are seeking a reliable and safety-conscious <strong>Class 4  Driver</strong> to support our logistics and transportation operations . The successful candidate will be responsible for the delivery and collection of goods using Class 4 vehicles while ensuring compliance with road safety regulations and company procedures.</p><h3><u><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></u></h3><ul><li> Operate Class 4 vehicles to deliver and collect goods across Singapore</li></ul><ul><li> Ensure timely and accurate deliveries according to assigned schedules</li></ul><ul><li> Load and unload goods safely, ensuring proper handling and securing of cargo</li></ul><ul><li> Conduct daily vehicle inspections and report any defects or maintenance issues</li></ul><ul><li> Maintain cleanliness and proper care of the assigned company vehicle</li></ul><ul><li> Prepare, verify, and submit delivery orders, invoices, and related documentation</li><li> Comply with traffic laws, workplace safety standards, and company policies</li></ul><ul><li> Coordinate with warehouse and operations teams to ensure smooth logistics flow</li></ul><ul><li> Perform other logistics-related duties as assigned</li></ul><h3><u><strong>Opportunities:</strong></u></h3><ul><li> Stable employment with long-term career prospects</li><li> On-the-job training and skills upgrading opportunities</li><li> Career progression within logistics and transportation operations</li></ul><h3><u><strong>Qualifications & Experience:</strong></u></h3><ul><li> Possess a valid <strong>Singapore Class 4 Driving License</strong></li></ul><ul><li> Minimum <strong>4-5 years of Class 4 driving experience</strong> preferred</li></ul><ul><li> Must be a Singaporean or PR or Service Sector Pass holder</li></ul><ul><li> Familiar with Singapore road networks, industrial areas, and delivery routes</li></ul><ul><li> Basic knowledge of logistics operations and documentation</li></ul><ul><li> Physically fit and able to perform loading and unloading of goods</li></ul><ul><li> Responsible, punctual, and safety-conscious</li></ul><ul><li> Able to communicate in basic English</li></ul><h2><strong>Why Join Us?</strong></h2><ul><li> Competitive salary package </li></ul><ul><li> Supportive work environment with structured operations</li></ul><ul><li> Well-maintained company vehicles and safety equipment</li></ul><ul><li> 12 hours working per day</li><li>Opportunity to grow with a stable and expanding logistics company</li></ul>",
